.SH "NAME"
bitmap_to_u32array \- copy the contents of bitmap to a u32 array of bits
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'unsigned\ int\ bitmap_to_u32array('u
.BI "unsigned int bitmap_to_u32array(u32\ *\ " "buf" ", unsigned\ int\ " "nwords" ", const\ unsigned\ long\ *\ " "bitmap" ", unsigned\ int\ " "nbits" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIbuf\fR
.RS 4
array of u32 (in host byte order), the dest bitmap, non NULL
.RE
.PP
\fInwords\fR
.RS 4
number of u32 words in
\fIbuf\fR
.RE
.PP
\fIbitmap\fR
.RS 4
array of unsigned longs, the source bitmap, non NULL
.RE
.PP
\fInbits\fR
.RS 4
number of bits in
\fIbitmap\fR
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
copy min(nbits, 32*nwords) bits from
\fIbitmap\fR
to
\fIbuf\fR\&. Remaining bits after nbits in
\fIbuf\fR
(if any) are cleared\&.
.PP
Return the number of bits effectively copied\&.
